title: Tour de Lizard Fat Tire Classic
Kansas State Cyclo-cross Championships
description: The 2007 Kansas State Cyclocross Championships will be round #5 of the De Stad Cyclocross Van Kansas Series.  The final event before the Cyclo-cross National Championships.
course: Course is 1.5 miles long and includes an uphill start/finish, gravel path, grassy hills, slops and off-camber turns.
registration: Registration closes 15 minutes before each race. Racing license must be shown at registration. A one day license may be purchased for 10.00.
notes: USCF permit applied for. All USCF Cyclocross rules apply. ANSI approved helmets required for all events. Mountain bikes are allowed, but must have bar ends removed. Races held rain or shine A domestic USCF or NORBA license is required. Parking: Follow signs to parking.
directions: Racers should use the address of 2012 10th Ave., Leavenworth, Kansas.  From Kansas City, take I-70 West to I-435 North, Exit off 435 at KS-5 (Exit 18). Follow KS-5 to you get to KS-7. Take KS-7 (4th Street) North.  Turn left at Limit Street. Take Limit street to 10th Ave.  Turn right on 10th Ave.  Kansas High School will be 1/2 mile at 2012 10th Ave.
